communications.subject: Washington Public Records Act Request: Mutual Aid Agreements (Edmonds Police Department)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Please provide any and all MOUs, contracts, or other written agreements with the City of Seattle related to the provision of police officers or other security assistance for the FIFA Club World Cup in 2025 and the World Cup in 2026.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Rose Terse

Following a reasonable search, the City of Edmonds Police Department found no identifiable records responsive to your request.  This is the City’s final, determinative response to your request.  Please note that the provisions of the Public Records Act, Ch. 42.56 RCW, pertain only to existing records and do not require the City to respond to requests for information or to create records in response to written inquiries. 
Please be advised, the City is now informing you that the one-year statute of limitations to seek judicial review in response to your records request beings to run on the date of this letter. ( Cousins v. State, Dept of Corrections _Wn.3d_, 546 P.3d 415 (2024).) 
Should you have any questions, please feel free to respond to this email or call me at 425-771-0282. 
Thank you, 
EDMONDS POLICE DEPARTMENT 
Alexandra Ehlert 
Executive Assistant - Confidential 
425-771-0282 
Per Washington State Law WAC 44.14.040, we are required to respond within five business days of receipt of the request with either the records, request for clarification, a time estimate to gather records, or notification that none exist.
